data.enText: a long narrow open container for animals to eat or drink from
if you say that people have their noses in the trough , you mean that they are trying to get a lot of money for themselves
a long narrow region of low air pressure between two regions of higher pressure

data.chText: 低谷；（企业或经济的）低潮，萧条阶段
data.enText: a period of time when the level of sth is low, especially a time when a business or the economy is not growing

data.chText: 长期以来失业率一直时起时伏。
data.enText: There have been peaks and troughs in the long-term trend of unemployment.

data.chText: （海浪间的）波谷；（小山间的）槽谷，盆状洼地
data.enText: a low area between two waves in the sea, or two hills

tr: a channel along the eaves or on the roof
a container (usually in a barn or stable) from which cattle or horses feed
a narrow depression (as in the earth or between ocean waves or in the ocean bed)
a concave shape with an open top

value.def: A trough is a long narrow container from which farm animals drink or eat.

example.ex: The old stone cattle trough still sits by the main entrance.
example.tran: 陈旧的石制牛食槽仍然放在大门口。

value.def: A trough is a low area between two big waves on the sea.

example.ex: The boat rolled heavily in the troughs between the waves.
example.tran: 船在波涛起伏的海浪中剧烈摇摆。

value.def: A trough is a low point in a process that has regular high and low points, for example a period in business when people do not produce as much as usual.

example.ex: Looking back afterwards you will see that this was not a terminal trough in your career...
example.tran: 今后回想起来你就会明白，这并非你事业中一蹶不振的低谷。

example.ex: American bank shares have risen by 60% since their trough last October.
example.tran: 美国的银行股自从去年 10 月跌入低谷以来已经上涨了 60%。

value.def: A trough of low pressure is a long narrow area of low air pressure between two areas of higher pressure.

example.ex: The trough of low pressure extended over about 1000 kilometres.
example.tran: 低压槽延伸约 1,000 公里。
